(firstQuint)Time Outdoors as an Intervention for Myopia in Children.

 1.

 To evaluate the effect of increased time outdoors on the incidence of myopia in non-myopic children; 2.

 To evaluate the effect of increased time outdoors on the progression of myopia in myopic children; 3.

 To explore if there is dose-response effect of time outdoors on the incidence and progression of myopia.

